15/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The special co-ordinator of the Stability Pact for Southeast Europe, Erhard Busek, believes that the recent US recognition of Macedonia's constitutional name was a step in the right direction. In an interview published in Monday's (15 November) daily <I>Dnevnik</I>, Busek said the development would intensify efforts to find a solution to the longstanding problem. He added that a debate on the issue is under way within the EU and would bring concrete results in the end. (Dnevnik - 15/11/04)
